        <div class="col-md-8 pull-right post-area">
            <p>XLSForm is a form standard created to help simplify the authoring of forms in Excel.  Authoring is done in a human readable format using a familiar tool that almost everyone knows - Excel.  XLSForms provide a practical standard for sharing and collaborating on authoring forms.  They are simple to get started with but allow for the authoring of complex forms by someone familiar with the syntax described below.</p>

<p>The XLSForm is then converted to an XForm, a popular open form standard, that allows you to author a form with complex functionality like skip logic in a consistent way across a number of web and mobile data collection platforms.    XLSForms are compatible with the subset of XForm functionality supported by <a href="https://bitbucket.org/javarosa/javarosa/wiki/Home">Javarosa Project</a>.  XLSForms are supported by a number of popular data collection platforms.</p>

        </div>
